{
  "texts": [
    "However, for requirements on transparency there is no need to resolve this debate.",
    "It highlights, rather, that both elements are relevant to the question at hand.",
    "To be sure that we can establish the legitimacy of a decisionmaking process we need to demonstrate both the impact that the process will have on the relevant people and the way in which the procedure itself is shaped, with the latter especially focused on how people are included in the procedure.",
    "With those ideas in mind, the next two sections consider current approaches to transparency in light of these requirements.",
    "They are, broadly speaking, split along the same lines as the views on legitimacy in terms of focusing either on the process itself or on the outcomes of the process."
  ]
}